# Folder Structure

## Purpose

Prevent sprawl and keep AI/human navigation predictable.

## When It Applies

Creating new files, packages, routes, or documentation.

## Requirements

| Location | Put here |
|----------|----------|
| `apps/web/app/` | Routes, layouts, app-specific shells |
| `packages/ui/src/components/` | Reusable UI (shadcn + composites) |
| `packages/core/src/` | Env, logger, errors, validation, base patterns |
| `packages/types/src/` | Shared TypeScript types |
| `packages/utils/src/` | Pure utility functions |
| `packages/db/` (Sprint 3+) | Database adapters only |
| `docs/` | All project documentation |
| `docs/templates/` | Document templates |
| `.cursor/rules/` | AI behavior rules |

## Examples

```
packages/ui/src/components/dialog.tsx     ✅ shadcn component
apps/web/components/app-shell.tsx         ✅ app-specific layout wiring
packages/core/src/repository/base-repository.ts  ✅ interface only
```

## Bad Examples

```
apps/web/components/ui/button.tsx         ❌ duplicates @repo/ui
packages/core/src/adapters/supabase.ts    ❌ belongs in @repo/db (Sprint 3)
docs/random-notes.md                      ❌ use BACKLOG or TASKS instead
```
